Package frc.misc

Class Chirp

java.lang.Object
com.ctre.phoenix.music.Orchestra
frc.misc.Chirp
All Implemented Interfaces:
ISubsystem
public class Chirp
extends com.ctre.phoenix.music.Orchestra
implements ISubsystem
This is where we play our gnarly tunez. Although it cant be seen from here, there is a delete deploy directory method in Robot that will help remove ghost files. Use this like an Orchestra with extra steps

    • updateTest

      public void updateTest()
      Autoplays music while taking suggestions. A few important things:

      - Music names must be in format <name>_<instruments>_<playtime in millis>.chrp

      - Songs will not be played if the instrument registry doesnt contain enough instruments

      - Autoplay will choose a new random song after the time specified in the file name

      Specified by:
      updateTest in interface ISubsystem
      See Also:
      Robot.testPeriodic()

      public com.ctre.phoenix.ErrorCode loadMusic​(java.lang.String soundName)

      Overrides:

      Error code per super call
